@startuml Seq02_TransactionManagement
!theme plain
participant User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "FastAPI Backend" as Backend
participant "Categorization\nService" as CatService
participant "MySQL Database" as DB

autonumber

Note over User,DB: **ADD MANUAL TRANSACTION**

User -> Frontend: Click "Add Transaction"
Frontend -> Frontend: Display transaction form
User -> Frontend: Enter date, description, amount, type

Frontend -> Frontend: Validate input
alt Input Valid
    Frontend -> Backend: POST /transactions/add\n{date, description, amount, type}
    
    Backend -> CatService: categorize(description)
    
    Note over CatService: Level 1: Rule-based
    CatService -> CatService: Check keywords
    alt Category Found
        CatService --> Backend: {category: "Food", confidence: 0.95}
    else Not Found
        Note over CatService: Level 3: AI Fallback
        CatService -> CatService: Send to LLM API
        CatService --> Backend: {category: "Food", confidence: 0.78}
    end
    
    Backend -> Frontend: {transaction, suggested_category}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show category suggestion
    
    User -> Frontend: Accept or correct category
    User -> Frontend: Click "Save"
    
    Frontend -> Backend: POST /transactions/add\n{...transaction, category_id}
    
    Backend -> DB: INSERT INTO transactions\nVALUES (...)
    DB --> Backend: {transaction_id, success}
    
    Backend --> Frontend: {status: "success", transaction}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show success notification
    Frontend -> Frontend: Clear form
    Frontend --> User: Transaction saved
    
else Input Invalid
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show validation errors
    Frontend --> User: Please fix errors
end

Note over User,DB: **VIEW ALL TRANSACTIONS**

User -> Frontend: Navigate to Transactions
Frontend -> Frontend: Show loading state
Frontend -> Backend: GET /transactions

Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM transactions\nWHERE user_id = {user_id}\nORDER BY date DESC
DB --> Backend: [transaction1, transaction2, ...]

Backend --> Frontend: {transactions: [...], total: 50}
Frontend -> Frontend: Render transaction table/list

Frontend --> User: Display transactions

Note over User,DB: **FILTER TRANSACTIONS**

User -> Frontend: Select filters\n(category, date range, type)
Frontend -> Frontend: Show filter panel
User -> Frontend: Apply filters

Frontend -> Backend: GET /transactions?category=Food\n&start_date=2026-01-01\n&end_date=2026-06-30\n&type=expense

Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM transactions\nWHERE user_id AND category_id=5\nAND date BETWEEN '2026-01-01' AND '2026-06-30'\nAND transaction_type='expense'
DB --> Backend: [filtered_transactions]

Backend --> Frontend: {transactions: [...], count: 15}
Frontend -> Frontend: Render filtered results
Frontend --> User: Show filtered transactions

Note over User,DB: **SEARCH TRANSACTIONS**

User -> Frontend: Enter search term\n(e.g., "McDonald's")
Frontend -> Backend: GET /transactions/search?q=McDonald's

Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM transactions\nWHERE user_id AND\n(description LIKE '%McDonald%'\nOR merchant LIKE '%McDonald%')
DB --> Backend: [matching_transactions]

Backend --> Frontend: {transactions: [...], count: 8}
Frontend -> Frontend: Highlight search term
Frontend --> User: Show search results

Note over User,DB: **EDIT TRANSACTION**

User -> Frontend: Click edit on transaction
Frontend -> Frontend: Show edit form with current data
User -> Frontend: Modify transaction details
User -> Frontend: Click "Update"

Frontend -> Backend: PUT /transactions/{id}\n{date, description, amount, type, category_id}

Backend -> DB: UPDATE transactions\nSET date=?, description=?, ...\nWHERE id={id}
DB --> Backend: {rows_affected: 1}

Backend --> Frontend: {status: "success", transaction}
Frontend -> Frontend: Show success message
Frontend -> Frontend: Update list
Frontend --> User: Transaction updated

Note over User,DB: **DELETE TRANSACTION**

User -> Frontend: Click delete on transaction
Frontend -> Frontend: Show confirmation dialog
User -> Frontend: Confirm deletion

Frontend -> Backend: DELETE /transactions/{id}

Backend -> DB: DELETE FROM transactions\nWHERE id={id} AND user_id={user_id}
DB --> Backend: {rows_deleted: 1}

Backend --> Frontend: {status: "success"}
Frontend -> Frontend: Remove from list
Frontend -> Frontend: Show success message
Frontend --> User: Transaction deleted

@enduml
